quondam Lincolniensis Epistol&aelig;</em> (Rerum Britannicarum Medii
&AElig;vi Scriptores 25), London: Longman, Green, Longman, and
Roberts.</p>

<p class="bibnote">
[Luard&rsquo;s edition of Grosseteste&rsquo;s first letter, though
older, is better than that found in
 <a href="#Baur1912">Baur 1912</a>,
 where Baur prints it, following many manuscripts, as the two works
<em>De unica forma omnium</em> and <em>De intelligentiis</em>.]</p>
</li>

<li>

<p class="nobottommargin">
McEvoy, James (ed.), 1974, &ldquo;The Sun as <em>res</em> and
