1982), Volume 2</em> (Philosophes m&eacute;di&eacute;vaux 27),
Christian Wenin (ed.), Louvain-la-Neuve: Editions de l&rsquo;Institut
sup&eacute;rieur de philosophie, 481&ndash;488.</li>

<li id="McEvoy1982"><p class="nobottommargin">McEvoy, James J., 1982,
<em>The Philosophy of Robert Grosseteste</em>, Oxford: Clarendon
Press. Corrected reprint, 1986.</p>

<p class="bibnote">
[A magisterial study of Grosseteste&rsquo;s thought. This work
includes significant material on Grosseteste&rsquo;s theological views
in his commentaries on the pseudo-Dionysius.]</p> </li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1983, &ldquo;The Chronology of Robert
Grosseteste&rsquo;s Writings on Nature and Natural Philosophy&rdquo;,
<em>Speculum</em>, 58(3): 614&ndash;655. </li>

<li id="McEvoy1994"><p class="nobottommargin">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;,
1994, <em>Robert Grosseteste, Exegete and Philosopher</em> (Variorum
Collected Studies Series CS446), Aldershot/Brookfield, VT:
Variorum.</p>

<p class="bibnote">
[A collection of articles written by this pre-eminent student of
Grosseteste.]</p> </li>

<li id="McEvoy1995">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 1995, <em>Robert
Grosseteste: New Perspectives on His Thought and Scholarship</em>
(Instrumenta Patristica 27), Turnhout: Brepols Publishers.
doi:10.1484/M.IPM-EB.5.112138</li>

<li id="McEvoy2000"><p class="nobottommargin">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;,
2000, <em>Robert Grosseteste</em> (Great Medieval Thinkers), New York:
Oxford University Press.</p>

<p class="bibnote">
[An excellent overview of Grosseteste&rsquo;s life and thought;
essential first reading for the prospective student of
Grosseteste.]</p> </li>

<li id="McEvoy2003">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2003, &ldquo;Robert
Grosseteste: The Man and His Legacy&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#MG2003">Mackie and Goering 2003</a>:
 1&ndash;30 (ch. 1). doi:10.3138/9781442674271-004</li>

<li>Noone, Timothy, 2010, &ldquo;Truth, Creation, and Intelligibility
in Anselm, Grosseteste, and Bonaventure&rdquo;, in <em>Truth: Studies
of a Robust Presence</em> (Studies in Philosophy and the History of
Philosophy 51), Kurt Pritzl (ed.), Washington, DC: Catholic University
of America Press, 102&ndash;126 (ch. 3).</li>

<li>Oliver, Simon, 2004, &ldquo;Robert Grosseteste on Light, Truth and
<em>Experimentum</em>&rdquo;, <em>Vivarium</em>, 42(2): 151&ndash;180.
doi:10.1163/1568534043084739</li>

<li>Palma, Robert J., 1975, &ldquo;Robert Grosseteste&rsquo;s
Understanding of Truth&rdquo;, <em>Irish Theological Quarterly</em>,
42(4): 300&ndash;306. doi:10.1177/002114007504200406</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1976, &ldquo;Grosseteste&rsquo;s Ordering
of <em>Scientia</em>&rdquo;, <em>New Scholasticism</em>, 50(4):
447&ndash;463. doi:10.5840/newscholas19765043</li>

<li>Panti, Cecilia, 1999, &ldquo;L&rsquo;incorporazione della luce
secondo Roberto Grossatesta&rdquo;, <em>Medioevo e rinascimento</em>,
new series, 13(10): 45&ndash;102.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2003, &ldquo;Robert Grosseteste&rsquo;s
Early Cosmology&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#MG2003">Mackie and Goering 2003</a>:
 135&ndash;166 (ch. 6). doi:10.3138/9781442674271-009</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2012, &ldquo;The Evolution of the Idea of
Corporeity in Robert Grosseteste&rsquo;s Writings&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Cunningham2012">Cunningham 2012</a>:
 111&ndash;139.</li>

<li id="Panti2013b">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013b, &ldquo;Robert
Grosseteste and Adam of Exeter&rsquo;s Physics of Light Remarks on the
Transmission, Authenticity, and Chronology of Grosseteste&rsquo;s
Scientific <em>Opuscula</em>&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#FGG2013">Flood, Ginther, and Goering 2013</a>:
 165&ndash;190. doi:10.1515/9781771103534-013</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017a, &ldquo;The Scientific Basis of
Robert Grosseteste&rsquo;s Teaching at the Oxford Franciscan
School&rdquo;, in <em>The English Province of the Franciscans
(1224&ndash;c.1350)</em>, Michael J. P. Robson (ed.), Leiden/Boston:
Brill, 247&ndash;272.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017b, &ldquo;Matter and Infinity in Robert
Grosseteste&rsquo;s <em>De luce</em> and <em>Notes on the
Physics</em>&rdquo;, in <em>Materia: nouvelles perspectives de
recherche dans la pens&eacute;e et la culture m&eacute;di&eacute;vales
(XIIe-XVIe si&egrave;cles)</em>, Tiziana Suarez-Nani and Agostino
Paravicini Bagliani (eds.), Firenze: SISMEL &ndash; Edizioni del Galluzzo,
27&ndash;55.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2018, &ldquo;The Theological Use of Science
at the Oxford Franciscan School: Thomas Docking, Roger Bacon, and
Robert Grosseteste&rsquo;s Works&rdquo;, in <em>The Franciscan Order
in the Medieval English Province and Beyond</em> (Church, Faith and
Culture in the Medieval West), Michael J. P. Robson and Patrick Zutshi
(eds.), Amsterdam: Amsterdam University Press, 181&ndash;210.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021a, &ldquo;The Oxford-Paris Connection
of Optics and the Theory of Rainbow: Grosseteste&rsquo;s <em>De
iride</em>, pseudo-Oresme&rsquo;s <em>Inter omnes impressiones</em>
and Bacon&rsquo;s <em>Perspectiva</em> in Paris, BnF, lat.
7434&rdquo;, in <em>Les Sciences au Moyen &Acirc;ge (XIIIe-XVe
si&egrave;cle). Autour de Micrologus</em>, Danielle Jacquart and
Agostino Paravicini Bagliani (eds.), Florence: SISMEL&ndash;Edizioni
del Galluzzo, 251&ndash;280.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021b, &ldquo;Adam Rufus of Exeter, Master
and Minor (d. 1234): A State of the Art&rdquo;, in <em>Early
Thirteenth-Century English Franciscan Thought</em>, Lydia Schumacher
(ed.), Berlin: De Gruyter, 93&ndash;126.
doi:10.1515/9783110684834-005</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023, &ldquo;In the Margins of the
&lsquo;Posterior Analytics&rsquo;: Robert Grosseteste and the
&lsquo;Latin Philoponus&rsquo;&rdquo;, <em>Revista Espa&ntilde;ola de
Filosof&iacute;a Medieval</em>, 30(1): 15&ndash;52.
doi:10.21071/refime.v30i1.16356</li>

<li>Pickav&eacute;, Martin, 2017, &ldquo;Robert Grosseteste on Free
Choice&rdquo;, in <em>From Learning to Love: Schools, Law, and
Pastoral Care in the Middle Ages: Essays in Honour of Joseph W.
Goering</em> (Papers in Mediaeval Studies 29), Tristan Sharp (ed.),
Toronto: Pontifical Institute of Mediaeval Studies, 70&ndash;89.</li>

<li>Polloni, Nicola, 2021a, &ldquo;Early Robert Grosseteste on
Matter&rdquo;, <em>Notes and Records: The Royal Society Journal of the
History of Science</em>, 75(3): 397&ndash;414.
doi:10.1098/rsnr.2020.0017</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021b, &ldquo;Robert Grosseteste on Motion,
Bodies, and Light&rdquo;, <em>British Journal for the History of
Philosophy</em>, 29(6): 1034&ndash;1053.
doi:10.1080/09608788.2021.1939651</li>

<li>Rossi, Pietro, 1995, &ldquo;Robert Grosseteste and the Object of
Scientific Knowledge&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#McEvoy1995">McEvoy 1995</a>:
 53&ndash;76.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2012, &ldquo;Grosseteste&rsquo;s Influence
on Thirteenth- and Fourteenth-Century British Commentaries on
<em>Posterior Analytics</em>&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Cunningham2012">Cunningham 2012</a>:
 140&ndash;166.</li>

<li>

<p class="nobottommargin">
Serene, Eileen F., 1979, &ldquo;Robert Grosseteste on Induction and
Demonstrative Science&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 40(1): 97&ndash;115.
doi:10.1007/BF00413947</p>

<p class="bibnote">
[A response to Crombie 1953.]</p> </li>

<li>Smith, Brett W., 2018, &ldquo;&lsquo;A Theme Song of His
Life&rsquo;: <em>Aspectus</em> and <em>Affectus</em> in the Writings
of Robert Grosseteste&rdquo;, <em>Franciscan Studies</em>, 76(1):
1&ndash;22. doi:10.1353/frc.2018.0000</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2022, &ldquo;Scotus and Grosseteste on
Phantasms and Illumination&rdquo;, <em>American Catholic Philosophical
Quarterly</em>, 96(4): 597&ndash;617. doi:10.5840/acpq2022822258</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023, <em>&lsquo;Aspectus&rsquo; and
&lsquo;Affectus&rsquo; in the Thought of Robert Grosseteste</em>,
Rome: IF Press.</li>

<li id="Southern1986">

<p class="nobottommargin">
Southern, R. W., 1986, <em>Robert Grosseteste: The Growth of an
English Mind in Medieval Europe</em>, Oxford: Clarendon Press. Second
edition, 1992.</p>

<p class="bibnote">
[One of the most important works on Grosseteste in recent years. The
second edition contains a long reply to some criticisms of the first
edition.]</p> </li>

<li>Van Dyke, Christina, 2009, &ldquo;An Aristotelian Theory of Divine
Illumination: Robert Grosseteste&rsquo;s <em>Commentary on the
Posterior Analytics</em>&rdquo;, <em>British Journal for the History
of Philosophy</em>, 17(4): 685&ndash;704.
doi:10.1080/09608780902986581</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010, &ldquo;The Truth, the Whole Truth,
and Nothing but the Truth: Robert Grosseteste on Universals (and the
<em>Posterior Analytics</em> )&rdquo;, <em>Journal of the History of
Philosophy</em>, 48(2): 153&ndash;170. doi:10.1353/hph.0.0207</li>

<li>

<p class="nobottommargin">
Wallace, William A., 1972, <em>Causality and Scientific Explanation,
Volume 1: Medieval and Early Classical Science</em>, Ann Arbor, MI:
University of Michigan Press.</p>

<p class="bibnote">
[Chapter 2 discusses Grosseteste&rsquo;s account of demonstrative
science.]</p> </li>
</ul>
</div> 

